title: The Fighting Shepherdess
creator: Caroline Lockhart
description: LibriVox recording of The Fighting Shepherdess, by Caroline Lockhart A classic style western written by one of the first female western writers. Caroline Lockhart was a rancher, writer and possibly the first woman to go over Glacier National Parks Swiftcurrent Pass. (Summary by Dawn) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B part 1 (160MB) Download M4B part 2 (164MB)
subject: Audiobook;LibriVox;Fiction;Western;Woman writer
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody: This was a very enjoyable story.  I like stories about all those pioneering women who fought so hard to be accepted in unconventional roles. There were some parts of the story that were sad (I hate it when bad things happen to animals) and there were parts that were pure triumph, vengeance and redemption.  The narration from Dawn Larsen, Linda Sizemore and the fabulous Richard Kilmer were very good.  Richard Kilmer has such a fantastic voice and it is perfect for western stories.  One of the narrators was rather tinny and bland but it is tolerable enough not to detract from the overall story.  An enjoyable listen, highly recommended.
reviews.reviewtitle: Wild West adventure at its best
